## Adding Custom Tools

### Step 1: Define the Tool Schema

Add to the `tools` array in `src/index.ts`:

```typescript
{
  name: "my_custom_tool",
  description: "Description of what the tool does",
  input_schema: {
    type: "object" as const,
    properties: {
      param1: {
        type: "string",
        description: "First parameter",
      },
      param2: {
        type: "number",
        description: "Second parameter (optional)",
      },
    },
    required: ["param1"],
  },
}
```

### Step 2: Implement the Handler

Add a case to the `executeTool` switch statement:

```typescript
case "my_custom_tool": {
  const param1 = input.param1 as string;
  const param2 = (input.param2 as number) || 0;

  // Your implementation here
  return `Result: ${param1}, ${param2}`;
}
```

### Step 3: Update CLAUDE.md

Document the new tool so the agent knows how to use it.

## Integration Patterns

### External API Integration

```typescript
case "fetch_stock_price": {
  const symbol = input.symbol as string;
  const response = await fetch(
    `https://api.example.com/stocks/${symbol}`,
    { headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.API_KEY}` } }
  );
  return JSON.stringify(await response.json());
}
```

### Database Integration

```typescript
case "query_postgres": {
  const query = input.query as string;
  const result = await pool.query(query);
  return JSON.stringify(result.rows);
}
```

### External Service Integration

```typescript
case "send_email": {
  await sendgrid.send({
    to: input.recipient as string,
    subject: input.subject as string,
    text: input.body as string,
  });
  return "Email sent successfully";
}
```

## Environment Variables

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` - Required. Your Anthropic API key.

Set secrets for deployed agents:
```bash
cast secrets set {{name}} ANTHROPIC_API_KEY sk-ant-...
```

